properties.description: The year in which the population data was collected
The number of people in the population

goals.question: What is the trend of population growth over the years?
goals.visualization: line chart of year vs. people
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if the population has been increasing, decreasing or remaining constant over the years.

goals.question: What is the distribution of age in the population?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the age distribution of the population and if there are any age groups that are over or underrepresented.

goals.question: What is the gender distribution of the population?
goals.visualization: bar chart of sex vs. people
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the gender distribution of the population and if there are any gender imbalances.

goals.question: What is the age distribution of males and females in the population?
goals.visualization: stacked bar chart of age vs. people, grouped by sex
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the age distribution of males and females in the population and if there are any age groups that are over or underrepresented in either gender.

goals.question: What is the population density in different age groups?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of age vs. people, with size of points representing population density
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the population density in different age groups and if there are any age groups that are more densely populated than others.

code:
```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['people'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of population growth over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Population')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['age'], bins=19, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean Age: {data['age'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of age in the population?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['sex']).sum().reset_index()
    plt.bar(data['sex'], data['people'], color=['blue', 'pink'])
    plt.xticks([1, 2], ['Male', 'Female'])
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution of the population?')
    plt.ylabel('Number of people')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['age', 'sex', 'people']]
    data = data.groupby(['age', 'sex']).sum().reset_index()
    male_data = data[data['sex'] == 1]
    female_data = data[data['sex'] == 2]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(male_data['age'], male_data['people'], label='Male', color='blue')
    ax.bar(female_data['age'], female_data['people'], label='Female', color='red')
    ax.set_xlabel('Age')
    ax.set_ylabel('Population')
    ax.set_title('What is the age distribution of males and females in the population?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['age'])['people'].sum().reset_index()
    data['density'] = data['people'] / data['people'].sum()
    plt.scatter(data['age'], data['people'], s=data['density']*100000, alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Population')
    plt.title('What is the population density in different age groups?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
